<ce:para>Some of the research activities in the area of global optimization has been presented in the special issue of Journal of Optimization Methods &amp; Software. The papers have been grouped into three parts, in which the first part presents five papers that analyze a variety of algorithms and methodologies. Lundell and Westerlund propose underestimation strategies for signomial functions, which are sums of products of powers and arise often in the engineering literature. In the second part, there are nine papers, all of which are associated with a specific global optimization software. Vaz and Vicente present PSwarm, a hybrid particle swarm algorithm for linearly constrained global derivative-free optimization. Anjos and Yen address the global optimization of one-dimensional facility layouts in the third section. Through a new semidefinite programming relaxation, the authors are able to solve problems with up to 100 facilities, a problem size that is outside the reach of earlier approaches.</ce:para>
